        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:151:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/151/2",
        "text": [
          " : «إِنَّمَا أُمِرَ اَلنَّاسُ أَنْ يَأْتُوا هَذِهِ اَلْأَحْجَارَ فَيَطُوفُوا بِهَا ثُمَّ يَأْتُونَا فَيُخْبِرُونَا بِوَلاَيَتِهِمْ وَ يَعْرِضُوا عَلَيْنَا نَصْرَهُمْ »."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.3139 - Umar ibn Udhaynah narrated from Zurara, who narrated from Abu Ja’far (as), who said:\n\"People have been commanded to come to these stones, to circumambulate around them, and then come to us to inform us of their allegiance and present their support to us.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1609,
        "local_index": 3,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "3140 - وَ سَأَلَ بَعْضُ أَصْحَابِنَا أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : فَقَالَ"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:151:3",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/151/3",
        "text": [
          " لَهُ أَبْدَأُ بِمَكَّةَ أَوْ بِالْمَدِينَةِ فَقَالَ لَهُ «اِبْدَأْ بِمَكَّةَ وَ اِخْتِمْ بِالْمَدِينَةِ فَإِنَّهُ أَفْضَلُ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.3140 - Some of our companions asked Abu Ja'far (as): \"Should I begin with Mecca or Medina?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"Begin with Mecca and conclude with Medina, for that is better.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1610,
        "local_index": 4,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
